Troubleshooting tips

| Symptom                                      | Likely cause & fix                                                      |
| -------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `gcc: command not found`                     | Ensure `gcc` is installed (`conda install gcc` or system package)       |
| R package compilation warnings/errors        | Verify that Râ€¯â‰¥â€¯4.1 is in the environment                               |
| `mapDamage: command not found` afterÂ install | Check that the environment is active and `$PATH` includes Condaâ€™s `bin` |




